Differences between using _sessions_ or _JSON Web Tokens_ for authentication.

Sessions store data for individual users against a unique session ID temporarily and can only be used in one domain.

Json tokens is not limited to one domain because they are stored in the request header

What does bcrypt do to help us store passwords in a secure manner?

 it can hashes them so that when added to a database it shouldn't be visible as written by the user.

How are unit tests different from integration and end-to-end testing?

end-to-end testing is testing the entire application and interacts with the app just like the user would.

Unit testing requires you to break down the application into smaller parts sin order to test it.

How _Test Driven Development_ changes the way we write applications and tests.

We write tests to make sure our code is working correctly.